    {
      "id": "PopularPost195901",
      "post_content": "Way back when I first started playing Magic, it always bugged me that Walls could only block 1 creature. I mean, look at that thing - it goes on for miles, so why can't it block more than 1 creature? This fell and Wall of Ice were great in holding off attackers. Then, we eventually learned that killing opposing creatures was better than hiding behind walls. Nobody much cared about walls until they started printing them with neat abilities (Wall of Blossoms, etc.)",
      "posted_by": "Radagast",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost195901\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">Way back when I first started playing Magic, it always bugged me that Walls could only block 1 creature. I mean, look at that thing - it goes on for miles, so why can't it block more than 1 creature? This fell and Wall of Ice were great in holding off attackers. Then, we eventually learned that killing opposing creatures was better than hiding behind walls. Nobody much cared about walls until they started printing them with neat abilities (Wall of Blossoms, etc.)</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '195901'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy42025\">Radagast</span>\r\n                                (9/15/2011 9:55:06 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Im